{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Use British English|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox cricketer | name = Frederick Barlow | country = England | fullname = Frederick Barlow | nickname = | birth_date = unknown | birth_place = [[Sheffield]] | death_date = unknown | heightft = | heightinch = | heightm = | batting = unknown | bowling = | role = | family = | club1 = [[Sheffield Cricket Club|Sheffield]] | year1 = 1834–36 | clubnumber1 = | deliveries = balls | columns = 1 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|first-class]] | matches1 = 4 | runs1 = 58 | bat avg1 = 8.28 | 100s/50s1 = –/– | top score1 = 22 | deliveries1 = – | wickets1 = – | bowl avg1 = – | fivefor1 = – | tenfor1 = – | best bowling1 = – | catches/stumpings1 = –/– | date = 21 July | year = 2013 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/10362.html ESPNcricinfo }}
'''Frederick Barlow''' (dates of birth and death unknown) was an English [[first-class cricket]]er, active 1834–36, who played for [[Sheffield Cricket Club]]. Barlow's [[batting (cricket)|batting]] style is unknown. He was christened at [[Sheffield]], [[Yorkshire]] on 2 March 1808.
Barlow made his first-class debut in 1834 for Sheffield in a match against [[Norfolk county cricket teams|Norfolk]] at the [[Hyde Park cricket ground|Hyde Park Ground]] in Sheffield. In matches against county teams, Sheffield were called Yorkshire.<ref name="FCM">{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/36/36288/First-Class_Matches.html|title=First-Class Matches played by Frederick Barlow|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 July 2013}}</ref> Later in 1834, Barlow played for Sheffield against [[Nottingham Cricket Club|Nottingham]] at Hyde Park.<ref name="FCM"/> His next appearances in first-class cricket were in 1836, when he played twice more against Norfolk, once at the [[New Ground, Norwich]] and the other at Hyde Park.<ref name="FCM"/> In four first-class matches, he scored 58 [[run (cricket)|runs]], [[batting average|averaging]] 8.28, with a highest score of 22.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/36/36288/36288.html|title=Player profile: Frederick Barlow|publisher=CricketArchive|accessdate=21 July 2013}}</ref>
